Changes Made to the ZeOS Kernel:


1. Implemented the macros RESTORE_ALL and EOI in entry.S to restore the context and signal the end of an interruption, respectively.
2. Implemented the clock_routine
    1. Added the clock_routine function in interrupt.c to display the clock information.
        - Also declared in interrupt.h.
    2. Added the clock_handler in entry.S to handle clock interrupts and call the clock_routine.
    3. Initialize the entry of clock interrupt in the IDT[32] in interrupt.c 
        - With setInterruptHandler(32, clock_handler, 0);
    4. Enable the clock interrupt (timer) in hardware.S by enabling the corresponding bit in "enable_int" function.

3. Creating syscall support
    1. Added the system_call_handler in entry.S (given by the zeos.pdf)
        - Single entry point for all syscalls
    2. Modify the IDT initialization in interrupt.c 
        - Entry point 0x80, and PL=3 (user level)
        - With setTrapHandler(0x80, system_call_handler, 3);
    3. Declared the system_call_handler in interrupt.h
    4. Created wrappers.S and added to Makefile line 71.

4. Creating syscall gettime();
    - Relevant files (by order): wrappers.S, sys_call_table.S, interrupt.h, interrupt.c, wrappers.S, sys.c  
    1. Added the entry sys_gettime (position 10) inside sys_call_table.S
    2. Declared and defined a global var zeos_ticks inside interrupt.h (as extern) and interrupt.c 
    3. zeos_ticks initialized to 0 inside the main system.c
    4. Modified the clock_routine to increase the zeos_ticks
    5. Modified the wrappers.S to add the wrapper for gettime
        - Created parameter passing macros
        - Implemented the wrapper for gettime
    6. Implemented the sys_gettime function in sys.c to return the value of zeos_ticks
    7. Added a test for gettime in user.c to check that it works correctly
    

5. Added error handling
    1. Added the header errno.h (from: https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/docs/+/master/constants/errnos.md)
    2. Included errno.h in entry.S and sys.c 
    3. To implement void perror(void) in libc.c when write is done

6. Implemented keyboard interrupt handling
    1. Added the scan-code to character translation table and the C routine keyboard_routine in interrupt.c to read from port 0x60 and print the pressed key.
    2. Added the keyboard_handler in entry.S to save/restore context, send EOI and call keyboard_routine.
    3. Initialized the keyboard interrupt entry in IDT[33] in interrupt.c with setInterruptHandler(33, keyboard_handler, 0).
    4. Modified enable_int in hardware.S to unmask the keyboard IRQ (set mask 0xFC so timer and keyboard are enabled).

7. Implemented Write and sysenter Write
    ...
8. Implemented page fault handling
